Subject: [Caml-list] [OPAM] moving OCamlPro/opam-repository to CC0

[Sorry for spamming the list with this, but I'm trying to reach as many of =
our contributors as possible or people who know them]

Hi,

Following the latest discussions on that list regarding the ownership of pa=
ckage descriptions in OPAM, I would like to relicense https://github.com/OC=
amlPro/opam-repository to public domain (CC0: http://creativecommons.org/pu=
blicdomain/zero/1.0/). This would mean that *anybody* can then fork the pac=
kage repository and uses it to its own good, without fear of any legal comp=
lication.

In order to do so, I (just) need the acknowledgment of the 83 contributors.=
 So far, I've got 36, which is not too bad in vacation time but not enough =
yet. So please, if you have contributed to OCamlPro/opam-repository, please=
 either:

- (i) say you are happy to relicense your contributions to CC0 on https://g=
ithub.com/OCamlPro/opam-repository/issues/955
- (ii) or send me a direct email to tell me so

If you are not happy with CC0, please send me an email so we can find a sol=
ution which should satisfy anyone.
If you don't care about the license stuff, please send me an email as well,=
 just saying that you are fine with CC0 (which is the closest thing to publ=
ic domain with a legal existence).

For information, this is the list of people who contributed and have not ye=
t given an answer. If you recognize in the list one of your friend or cowor=
ker, please ping he/her.

